 135:UART_Btldr.c  **** *
 136:UART_Btldr.c  **** * Summary:
 137:UART_Btldr.c  **** *  Allows the caller to write data to the bootloader host. This function uses 
 138:UART_Btldr.c  **** * a block write function for writing data using UART communication component. 
 139:UART_Btldr.c  **** *
 140:UART_Btldr.c  **** * Parameters:
 141:UART_Btldr.c  **** *  pData:    A pointer to the block of data to send to the device
 142:UART_Btldr.c  **** *  size:     The number of bytes to write.
 143:UART_Btldr.c  **** *  count:    Pointer to an unsigned short variable to write the number of
 144:UART_Btldr.c  **** *             bytes actually written.
 145:UART_Btldr.c  **** *  timeOut:  Number of units to wait before returning because of a timeout.
 146:UART_Btldr.c  **** *
 147:UART_Btldr.c  **** * Return: 
 148:UART_Btldr.c  **** *   cystatus: This function will return CYRET_SUCCESS if data is sent successfully.
 149:UART_Btldr.c  **** *
 150:UART_Btldr.c  **** * Side Effects:
 151:UART_Btldr.c  **** *  This function should be called after command was received .
 152:UART_Btldr.c  **** *
 153:UART_Btldr.c  **** *******************************************************************************/
